The paper presents a method for constructing SHACL or ShEx constraints for an existing RDF dataset using an algorithm for automatic schema construction and an interactive workflow for editing the schema. This involves techniques from artificial intelligence (AI) such as machine learning and pattern recognition, as well as database (DB) and software engineering (SE) concepts. The paper also discusses the use of domain experts and ontologies, which are relevant to information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) fields. Overall, the paper covers a broad range of CS sub-categories, but the emphasis on AI, DB, and SE makes them the most likely categories.
